title: Liver Tumor Tissue LCS-079A
extract_protocol_ch1.1: Other: Total RNA was isolated from microdissected fresh frozen tissues using TRIzol (Invitrogen, Carlsbad, CA) according to the manufacturer's protocol. RNA integrity for each sample was confirmed with the Agilent 2100 Bioanalyzer (Agilent Technologies, Palo Alto, CA).
label_protocol_ch1: Biotinylated cRNA Labeling for HT Arrays
label_protocol_ch1.1: Other: Biotinylated cRNA were prepared according to the standard Affymetrix protocol from 1 ug total RNA (Expression Analysis Technical Manual, For HT Array Plates Using the GeneChip® Array Station, P/N 702063 Rev. 2, Affymetrix).
hyb_protocol.1: Other: The fragmented cRNA is added to a hybridization solution containing several biotinylated control oligonucleotides (for quality control), and hybridized to a microarray chip overnight at 45°C. The chips are then transferred to a fluidics instrument that performs washes to remove cRNA that has not hybridized to its complementary oligonucleotide probe. The bound cRNA is then fluorescently labeled using phycoerythrin-conjugated streptavidin (SAPE); additional fluors are then added using biotinylated anti-streptavidin antibody and additional SAPE.
scan_protocol.1: Other: GeneChips were scanned using GeneChip® HT Array Plate Scanner by Affymetrix.
data_processing.1: Calculation Method: The CEL files from the two Affymetrix series were combined using the matchprobes package in the R programming environment. Thereafter, the RMA method in the R affy package was used to obtain probe set expression summaries.

The chips are then transferred to a fluidics instrument that performs washes to remove cRNA that has not hybridized to its complementary oligonucleotide probe. The bound cRNA is then fluorescently labeled using phycoerythrin-conjugated streptavidin (SAPE); additional fluors are then added using biotinylated anti-streptavidin antibody and additional SAPE.
scan_protocol.1: Other: GeneChips were scanned using GeneChip® HT Array Plate Scanner by Affymetrix.
data_processing.1: Calculation Method: The CEL files from the two Affymetrix series were combined using the matchprobes package in the R programming environment. Thereafter, the RMA method in the R affy package was used to obtain probe set expression summaries.

label_protocol_ch1: Biotinylated cRNA Labeling for HT Arrays
label_protocol_ch1.1: Other: Biotinylated cRNA were prepared according to the standard Affymetrix protocol from 1 ug total RNA (Expression Analysis Technical Manual, For HT Array Plates Using the GeneChip® Array Station, P/N 702063 Rev. 2, Affymetrix).
hyb_protocol.1: Other: The fragmented cRNA is added to a hybridization solution containing several biotinylated control oligonucleotides (for quality control), and hybridized to a microarray chip overnight at 45°C. The chips are then transferred to a fluidics instrument that performs washes to remove cRNA that has not hybridized to its complementary oligonucleotide probe. The bound cRNA is then fluorescently labeled using phycoerythrin-conjugated streptavidin (SAPE); additional fluors are then added using biotinylated anti-streptavidin antibody and additional SAPE.
scan_protocol.1: Other: GeneChips were scanned using GeneChip® HT Array Plate Scanner by Affymetrix.
data_processing.1: Calculation Method: The CEL files from the two Affymetrix series were combined using the matchprobes package in the R programming environment. Thereafter, the RMA method in the R affy package was used to obtain probe set expression summaries.

The chips are then transferred to a fluidics instrument that performs washes to remove cRNA that has not hybridized to its complementary oligonucleotide probe. The bound cRNA is then fluorescently labeled using phycoerythrin-conjugated streptavidin (SAPE); additional fluors are then added using biotinylated anti-streptavidin antibody and additional SAPE.
scan_protocol.1: Other: GeneChips were scanned using GeneChip® HT Array Plate Scanner by Affymetrix.
data_processing.1: Calculation Method: The CEL files from the two Affymetrix series were combined using the matchprobes package in the R programming environment. Thereafter, the RMA method in the R affy package was used to obtain probe set expression summaries.

label_protocol_ch1.1: Other: Biotinylated cRNA were prepared according to the standard Affymetrix protocol from 1 ug total RNA (Expression Analysis Technical Manual, For HT Array Plates Using the GeneChip® Array Station, P/N 702063 Rev. 2, Affymetrix).
hyb_protocol.1: Other: The fragmented cRNA is added to a hybridization solution containing several biotinylated control oligonucleotides (for quality control), and hybridized to a microarray chip overnight at 45°C. The chips are then transferred to a fluidics instrument that performs washes to remove cRNA that has not hybridized to its complementary oligonucleotide probe. The bound cRNA is then fluorescently labeled using phycoerythrin-conjugated streptavidin (SAPE); additional fluors are then added using biotinylated anti-streptavidin antibody and additional SAPE.
scan_protocol.1: Other: GeneChips were scanned using GeneChip® HT Array Plate Scanner by Affymetrix.
data_processing.1: Calculation Method: The CEL files from the two Affymetrix series were combined using the matchprobes package in the R programming environment. Thereafter, the RMA method in the R affy package was used to obtain probe set expression summaries.

title: Liver Non-Tumor Tissue LCS-281B
extract_protocol_ch1.1: Other: Total RNA was isolated from microdissected fresh frozen tissues using TRIzol (Invitrogen, Carlsbad, CA) according to the manufacturer's protocol. RNA integrity for each sample was confirmed with the Agilent 2100 Bioanalyzer (Agilent Technologies, Palo Alto, CA).
label_protocol_ch1: Biotinylated cRNA Labeling for HT Arrays
label_protocol_ch1.1: Other: Biotinylated cRNA were prepared according to the standard Affymetrix protocol from 1 ug total RNA (Expression Analysis Technical Manual, For HT Array Plates Using the GeneChip® Array Station, P/N 702063 Rev. 2, Affymetrix).
hyb_protocol.1: Other: The fragmented cRNA is added to a hybridization solution containing several biotinylated control oligonucleotides (for quality control), and hybridized to a microarray chip overnight at 45°C. The chips are then transferred to a fluidics instrument that performs washes to remove cRNA that has not hybridized to its complementary oligonucleotide probe. The bound cRNA is then fluorescently labeled using phycoerythrin-conjugated streptavidin (SAPE); additional fluors are then added using biotinylated anti-streptavidin antibody and additional SAPE.

The bound cRNA is then fluorescently labeled using phycoerythrin-conjugated streptavidin (SAPE); additional fluors are then added using biotinylated anti-streptavidin antibody and additional SAPE.
scan_protocol.1: Other: GeneChips were scanned using GeneChip® HT Array Plate Scanner by Affymetrix.
data_processing.1: Calculation Method: The CEL files from the two Affymetrix series were combined using the matchprobes package in the R programming environment. Thereafter, the RMA method in the R affy package was used to obtain probe set expression summaries.

label_protocol_ch1.1: Other: Biotinylated cRNA were prepared according to the standard Affymetrix protocol from 1 ug total RNA (Expression Analysis Technical Manual, For HT Array Plates Using the GeneChip® Array Station, P/N 702063 Rev. 2, Affymetrix).
hyb_protocol.1: Other: The fragmented cRNA is added to a hybridization solution containing several biotinylated control oligonucleotides (for quality control), and hybridized to a microarray chip overnight at 45°C. The chips are then transferred to a fluidics instrument that performs washes to remove cRNA that has not hybridized to its complementary oligonucleotide probe. The bound cRNA is then fluorescently labeled using phycoerythrin-conjugated streptavidin (SAPE); additional fluors are then added using biotinylated anti-streptavidin antibody and additional SAPE.
scan_protocol.1: Other: GeneChips were scanned using GeneChip® HT Array Plate Scanner by Affymetrix.
data_processing.1: Calculation Method: The CEL files from the two Affymetrix series were combined using the matchprobes package in the R programming environment. Thereafter, the RMA method in the R affy package was used to obtain probe set expression summaries.

title: Liver Non-Tumor Tissue LCS-047B
extract_protocol_ch1.1: Other: Total RNA was isolated from microdissected fresh frozen tissues using TRIzol (Invitrogen, Carlsbad, CA) according to the manufacturer's protocol. RNA integrity for each sample was confirmed with the Agilent 2100 Bioanalyzer (Agilent Technologies, Palo Alto, CA).
label_protocol_ch1: Biotinylated cRNA Labeling for HT Arrays
label_protocol_ch1.1: Other: Biotinylated cRNA were prepared according to the standard Affymetrix protocol from 1 ug total RNA (Expression Analysis Technical Manual, For HT Array Plates Using the GeneChip® Array Station, P/N 702063 Rev. 2, Affymetrix).
hyb_protocol.1: Other: The fragmented cRNA is added to a hybridization solution containing several biotinylated control oligonucleotides (for quality control), and hybridized to a microarray chip overnight at 45°C. The chips are then transferred to a fluidics instrument that performs washes to remove cRNA that has not hybridized to its complementary oligonucleotide probe. The bound cRNA is then fluorescently labeled using phycoerythrin-conjugated streptavidin (SAPE); additional fluors are then added using biotinylated anti-streptavidin antibody and additional SAPE.
scan_protocol.1: Other: GeneChips were scanned using GeneChip® HT Array Plate Scanner by Affymetrix.

The bound cRNA is then fluorescently labeled using phycoerythrin-conjugated streptavidin (SAPE); additional fluors are then added using biotinylated anti-streptavidin antibody and additional SAPE.
scan_protocol.1: Other: GeneChips were scanned using GeneChip® HT Array Plate Scanner by Affymetrix.
data_processing.1: Calculation Method: The CEL files from the two Affymetrix series were combined using the matchprobes package in the R programming environment. Thereafter, the RMA method in the R affy package was used to obtain probe set expression summaries.

label_protocol_ch1.1: Other: Biotinylated cRNA were prepared according to the standard Affymetrix protocol from 1 ug total RNA (Expression Analysis Technical Manual, For HT Array Plates Using the GeneChip® Array Station, P/N 702063 Rev. 2, Affymetrix).
hyb_protocol.1: Other: The fragmented cRNA is added to a hybridization solution containing several biotinylated control oligonucleotides (for quality control), and hybridized to a microarray chip overnight at 45°C. The chips are then transferred to a fluidics instrument that performs washes to remove cRNA that has not hybridized to its complementary oligonucleotide probe. The bound cRNA is then fluorescently labeled using phycoerythrin-conjugated streptavidin (SAPE); additional fluors are then added using biotinylated anti-streptavidin antibody and additional SAPE.
scan_protocol.1: Other: GeneChips were scanned using GeneChip® HT Array Plate Scanner by Affymetrix.
data_processing.1: Calculation Method: The CEL files from the two Affymetrix series were combined using the matchprobes package in the R programming environment. Thereafter, the RMA method in the R affy package was used to obtain probe set expression summaries.

title: Liver Non-Tumor Tissue LCS-170B
extract_protocol_ch1.1: Other: Total RNA was isolated from microdissected fresh frozen tissues using TRIzol (Invitrogen, Carlsbad, CA) according to the manufacturer's protocol. RNA integrity for each sample was confirmed with the Agilent 2100 Bioanalyzer (Agilent Technologies, Palo Alto, CA).
label_protocol_ch1: Biotinylated cRNA Labeling for HT Arrays
label_protocol_ch1.1: Other: Biotinylated cRNA were prepared according to the standard Affymetrix protocol from 1 ug total RNA (Expression Analysis Technical Manual, For HT Array Plates Using the GeneChip® Array Station, P/N 702063 Rev. 2, Affymetrix).
hyb_protocol.1: Other: The fragmented cRNA is added to a hybridization solution containing several biotinylated control oligonucleotides (for quality control), and hybridized to a microarray chip overnight at 45°C. The chips are then transferred to a fluidics instrument that performs washes to remove cRNA that has not hybridized to its complementary oligonucleotide probe. The bound cRNA is then fluorescently labeled using phycoerythrin-conjugated streptavidin (SAPE); additional fluors are then added using biotinylated anti-streptavidin antibody and additional SAPE.
scan_protocol.1: Other: GeneChips were scanned using GeneChip® HT Array Plate Scanner by Affymetrix.

The bound cRNA is then fluorescently labeled using phycoerythrin-conjugated streptavidin (SAPE); additional fluors are then added using biotinylated anti-streptavidin antibody and additional SAPE.
scan_protocol.1: Other: GeneChips were scanned using GeneChip® HT Array Plate Scanner by Affymetrix.
data_processing.1: Calculation Method: The CEL files from the two Affymetrix series were combined using the matchprobes package in the R programming environment. Thereafter, the RMA method in the R affy package was used to obtain probe set expression summaries.

label_protocol_ch1.1: Other: Biotinylated cRNA were prepared according to the standard Affymetrix protocol from 1 ug total RNA (Expression Analysis Technical Manual, For HT Array Plates Using the GeneChip® Array Station, P/N 702063 Rev. 2, Affymetrix).
hyb_protocol.1: Other: The fragmented cRNA is added to a hybridization solution containing several biotinylated control oligonucleotides (for quality control), and hybridized to a microarray chip overnight at 45°C. The chips are then transferred to a fluidics instrument that performs washes to remove cRNA that has not hybridized to its complementary oligonucleotide probe. The bound cRNA is then fluorescently labeled using phycoerythrin-conjugated streptavidin (SAPE); additional fluors are then added using biotinylated anti-streptavidin antibody and additional SAPE.
scan_protocol.1: Other: GeneChips were scanned using GeneChip® HT Array Plate Scanner by Affymetrix.
data_processing.1: Calculation Method: The CEL files from the two Affymetrix series were combined using the matchprobes package in the R programming environment. Thereafter, the RMA method in the R affy package was used to obtain probe set expression summaries.

The chips are then transferred to a fluidics instrument that performs washes to remove cRNA that has not hybridized to its complementary oligonucleotide probe. The bound cRNA is then fluorescently labeled using phycoerythrin-conjugated streptavidin (SAPE); additional fluors are then added using biotinylated anti-streptavidin antibody and additional SAPE.
scan_protocol.1: Other: GeneChips were scanned using GeneChip® HT Array Plate Scanner by Affymetrix.
data_processing.1: Calculation Method: The CEL files from the two Affymetrix series were combined using the matchprobes package in the R programming environment. Thereafter, the RMA method in the R affy package was used to obtain probe set expression summaries.

label_protocol_ch1: Biotinylated cRNA Labeling for HT Arrays
label_protocol_ch1.1: Other: Biotinylated cRNA were prepared according to the standard Affymetrix protocol from 1 ug total RNA (Expression Analysis Technical Manual, For HT Array Plates Using the GeneChip® Array Station, P/N 702063 Rev. 2, Affymetrix).
hyb_protocol.1: Other: The fragmented cRNA is added to a hybridization solution containing several biotinylated control oligonucleotides (for quality control), and hybridized to a microarray chip overnight at 45°C. The chips are then transferred to a fluidics instrument that performs washes to remove cRNA that has not hybridized to its complementary oligonucleotide probe. The bound cRNA is then fluorescently labeled using phycoerythrin-conjugated streptavidin (SAPE); additional fluors are then added using biotinylated anti-streptavidin antibody and additional SAPE.
scan_protocol.1: Other: GeneChips were scanned using GeneChip® HT Array Plate Scanner by Affymetrix.
data_processing.1: Calculation Method: The CEL files from the two Affymetrix series were combined using the matchprobes package in the R programming environment. Thereafter, the RMA method in the R affy package was used to obtain probe set expression summaries.

title: Liver Non-Tumor Tissue LCS-142B
extract_protocol_ch1.1: Other: Total RNA was isolated from microdissected fresh frozen tissues using TRIzol (Invitrogen, Carlsbad, CA) according to the manufacturer's protocol. RNA integrity for each sample was confirmed with the Agilent 2100 Bioanalyzer (Agilent Technologies, Palo Alto, CA).
label_protocol_ch1: Biotinylated cRNA Labeling for HT Arrays
label_protocol_ch1.1: Other: Biotinylated cRNA were prepared according to the standard Affymetrix protocol from 1 ug total RNA (Expression Analysis Technical Manual, For HT Array Plates Using the GeneChip® Array Station, P/N 702063 Rev. 2, Affymetrix).
hyb_protocol.1: Other: The fragmented cRNA is added to a hybridization solution containing several biotinylated control oligonucleotides (for quality control), and hybridized to a microarray chip overnight at 45°C. The chips are then transferred to a fluidics instrument that performs washes to remove cRNA that has not hybridized to its complementary oligonucleotide probe. The bound cRNA is then fluorescently labeled using phycoerythrin-conjugated streptavidin (SAPE); additional fluors are then added using biotinylated anti-streptavidin antibody and additional SAPE.
scan_protocol.1: Other: GeneChips were scanned using GeneChip® HT Array Plate Scanner by Affymetrix.

The bound cRNA is then fluorescently labeled using phycoerythrin-conjugated streptavidin (SAPE); additional fluors are then added using biotinylated anti-streptavidin antibody and additional SAPE.
scan_protocol.1: Other: GeneChips were scanned using GeneChip® HT Array Plate Scanner by Affymetrix.
data_processing.1: Calculation Method: The CEL files from the two Affymetrix series were combined using the matchprobes package in the R programming environment. Thereafter, the RMA method in the R affy package was used to obtain probe set expression summaries.

hyb_protocol.1: Other: The fragmented cRNA is added to a hybridization solution containing several biotinylated control oligonucleotides (for quality control), and hybridized to a microarray chip overnight at 45°C. The chips are then transferred to a fluidics instrument that performs washes to remove cRNA that has not hybridized to its complementary oligonucleotide probe. The bound cRNA is then fluorescently labeled using phycoerythrin-conjugated streptavidin (SAPE); additional fluors are then added using biotinylated anti-streptavidin antibody and additional SAPE.
scan_protocol.1: Other: GeneChips were scanned using GeneChip® Scanner 3000 by Affymetrix.
data_processing.1: Calculation Method: The CEL files from the two Affymetrix series were combined using the matchprobes package in the R programming environment. Thereafter, the RMA method in the R affy package was used to obtain probe set expression summaries.
